                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="70r" to="77v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Speculum amatorum mundi (Speculum humanae salvationis / Speculum peccatoris)</title>
                                <incipit>VIdete quomodo caute ambuletis (Eph. 5:15) <gap reason="editorial"/> Apostolus paulus Conscius consiliorum dei</incipit>
                                <explicit>fugiat ergo qui saluari desiderat ut penas eternas intollerabiles et horribiles declinet et evadat et regnum amenum et iocundum cum sanctis et electis eorum meritis et precibus possideat Quod nobis prestare dignetur qui patre et spiritu sancto regnat per infinita secula seculorum Amen</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107423">Bloomfield et al. (1979)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="6443" to="6443" unit="number"/>
                                        </bibl>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        The authorship of the text is debated; it has been attributed to, among others, <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102677">Denis the Carthusian</persName> (1402-1471). Emery, however, argues based on the date of the watermark that the text cannot be by Denis (<bibl>
                                            <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107424">Emery 1991</title>
                                            <citedRange from="585" to="585" unit="page"/>
                                        </bibl>).</p>
                                </note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107420">Doctoris extatici D. Dionysii Cartusiani Opera omnia</title>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="78r" to="78r" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Regula vitae</title>
                                <incipit>Si vis esse perfectus in vita tua has regulas firmiter serua</incipit>
                                <explicit>sed pocius in exemplum time deum et sequere eum et sepe confitere Et cetera</explicit>
                                <finalRubric>explicit regula vite etc</finalRubric>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107423">Bloomfield et al. (1979)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="5673" to="5673" unit="number"/>
                                        </bibl>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        After the final rubric is added a paraphrase of <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102515">Augustine</persName>, <quote>Augustinus Visus facit malam cogitacionem cogitacio delectacionem delectacio consensum consensus operam operacio consuetudo desperacionem <sic>despereacio</sic> eternam dampnacionem etc</quote>, a parallel of which can be found in Sermo 98, <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107168">PL</title>
                                            <citedRange from="38" to="38" unit="volume"/>
                                            <citedRange from="594" to="594" unit="column"/>
                                        </bibl>.</p>
                                </note>
                            </msItem>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="78v" to="78v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Exhortations for a religious life <!--Samma text finns i annan hs under rubriken Admonitio regularis disciplinae / Admonitio salutaris--></title>
                                <incipit>O tu religiosus homo tota intencione studeas ut habeas oculos stabiles</incipit>
                                <explicit>Quicquid agas prudenter agas et respice finem et cetera et est finis</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>
                                        <bibl>
                                            <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107423">Bloomfield et al. (1979)</title>
                                            <citedRange from="3554" to="3554" unit="number"/>
                                        </bibl>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        Two leaves missing after <locus from="78" to="78" scheme="folios"/>.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="79" to="79" scheme="folios"/>: blank.</p>
                                </note>
